Sometimes inspiration takes me, and I end up writing an outline or the start of a story, but then I stop. It's usually a fun idea that popped into my head, but that either needs more time in the oven, isn't going anywhere worthwhile, or I have other projects that I prioritize in the moment. I always keep what I write, though, and sometimes I go back with fresh eyes or just more time on my hands to rework or continue writing. As far as favorites are concerned, I guess I keep thinking about one in particular. It's a horror story with a protagonist who's hovering between clueless and jaded, so he reacts to the horror in a very straight-faced, or even comedic, way. I think I'm more interested in the how of writing than the story itself, though, as I'm not sure I could make it work
